newProducts.title: Google Antigravity
newProducts.description: Google's new agent-first AI coding tool powered by Gemini 3. Enables autonomous AI agents to write code, manage tasks, and execute complex multi-tool software tasks across editor, terminal, and filesystem. Features agent manager & editor shared workflows, natural language code commands, and configurable context-aware agents.

newProducts.title: Chad: The Brainrot IDE
newProducts.description: Y Combinator-backed controversial AI-powered coding environment that pairs 'vibe coding' with entertainment activities like gambling, watching TikToks, and playing games while AI coding assistants work. Represents a unique approach to AI-assisted development with gamification elements.

newProducts.title: Meta DevMate
newProducts.description: Meta's sophisticated AI coding assistant that goes beyond code completion. Scans entire codebases, suggests fixes, refactors legacy code, and performs debugging. Integrates models from multiple providers including Anthropic's Claude, offering advanced coding assistance and program analysis.

newProducts.title: Microsoft Agent Framework
newProducts.description: Microsoft's open-source framework for building, orchestrating, and deploying AI agents and multi-agent workflows with support for Python and .NET. Includes VS Code AI Toolkit integration and Azure AI Foundry Agent Service for managed runtime hosting of agents and multi-agent workflows.

newProducts.title: Windsurf Cascade
newProducts.description: Formerly Codeium, Windsurf features Cascade - an AI agent that codes, fixes, and thinks 10 steps ahead. Enhanced AI-native IDE with Fast Context technology, improved third-party extension diagnostics, and collaborative flow between developers and AI.

newProducts.title: AI Toolkit Extension Pack for VS Code
newProducts.description: Microsoft's comprehensive VS Code extension for building next-generation agentic AI applications. Streamlined experience for building with Microsoft Agent Framework, enabling developers to create powerful AI agents and workflows directly within VS Code.

newProducts.title: Google AI Studio Build
newProducts.description: Part of Google's Gemini 3 launch, this online AI coding tool helps developers quickly turn ideas into runnable web applications. Features 'vibe coding' capabilities and integrates with Antigravity for comprehensive development workflows.

whitelistUpdates.title: Advanced Tool Use and Autonomy Features
whitelistUpdates.description: Added three new beta features that let Claude discover, learn, and use tools more autonomously, along with improved status visibility and searchable prompt history (Ctrl+r)

whitelistUpdates.title: Cursor 2.0 with Composer AI Model
whitelistUpdates.description: Major update introducing Cursor's own frontier coding model called Composer and a redesigned interface built around agentic workflows with multi-agent support

whitelistUpdates.title: Agent Mode and Planning Features
whitelistUpdates.description: New Agent Mode for handling larger, multi-step coding tasks with structured reasoning, plus planning features in Copilot Chat and unified agent experience in VS Code

whitelistUpdates.title: Falcon Alpha Model and Cascade Hooks
whitelistUpdates.description: Introduced Falcon Alpha, a new stealth agentic model designed for speed, and made Cascade Hooks feature available to all tiers for enhanced workflow automation

whitelistUpdates.title: DeepWiki Codemaps Interactive Visualization
whitelistUpdates.description: Added interactive code visualization in DeepWiki, allowing developers to explore codebases visually with intuitive mode switching for repository documentation

whitelistUpdates.title: Instant Edits and GPT-5 Codex Support
whitelistUpdates.description: Added Instant Edits functionality, GPT-5 Codex support, and Grok Code Fast 1 integration for enhanced coding performance and developer experience

whitelistUpdates.title: Tree-sitter Language Pack Integration
whitelistUpdates.description: Major upgrade adding support for 130 new languages with linter support and 20 new languages with repo-map capabilities through tree-sitter-language-pack adoption
